"title": "5147: deafness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5147",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The condition of being wholly, or partly, without hearing. It can be expressed in physical or spiritual terms and is often used to depict spiritual rebellion.</p>\n<h2>God's control of deafness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:11\">EXO 4:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:9\">PSA 94:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:12\">PRO 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:20\">LUK 1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:62\">LUK 1:62</a></p>\n<h2>Physical aspects of deafness</h2>\n<h3>Compassion for the deaf</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:14\">LEV 19:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Deafness sometimes caused by Satan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25\">MRK 9:25</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Healed by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:5\">MAT 11:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:22\">LUK 7:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:32-Mark7:37\">MRK 7:32–7:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:49-Luke22:51\">LUK 22:49–22:51</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual aspects of deafness</h2>\n<h3>God deaf to a rebellious people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:45\">DEU 1:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:1\">PSA 28:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:13\">PSA 38:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:12\">PSA 39:12</a></p>\n<h3>Rebellious humanity deaf to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:10\">JER 6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:9\">PRO 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:10\">ISA 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:19-Isa42:20\">ISA 42:19–42:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:32\">EZK 33:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:4\">EZK 37:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:16\">MIC 7:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:11\">ZEC 7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:15\">MAT 13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:9-Mark4:12\">MRK 4:9–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:10\">LUK 8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:40\">JHN 12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:26-Acts28:27\">ACT 28:26–28:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:4\">2TI 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a> <em>Sin brings spiritual deafness.</em></p>\n<h2>The deafness of idols</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:28\">DEU 4:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:6\">PSA 115:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:17\">PSA 135:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:23\">DAN 5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:20\">REV 9:20</a></p>\n<h2>Release from deafness</h2>\n<h3>Through repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:18\">ISA 29:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:5\">ISA 35:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:18\">ISA 42:18</a></p>\n<h3>Through the coming of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:22\">LUK 7:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:5\">MAT 11:5</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:32-Mark7:37\">MRK 7:32–7:37</a></p>",
